articles.title: Exercise is making you age faster, new study suggests - indy100

A group of Scandinavian scientists have come up with some new research that will strike fear into the hearts of runners and gym rats alike.

TAF15 amyloid filaments in frontotemporal lobar degeneration - Nature.com
articles.description: Cryogenic electron microscopy structures of amyloid filaments extracted from patient brains reveal that the protein TAF15 forms filaments that characterize certain cases of frontotemporal lobar degeneration.
